transcript_parts.text: i once saw god and this is what he said
to me everything you were as far as i'm
concerned is dead to me took my hand and
gently led me to the throne of destiny
showed me everything i was always ever
meant to be opened up my eyes he showed
me all the lies fed to me looked and saw
the ministry that he had set up for me
he took off
burden of hurting words and curses from
my enemies and gave me a robin ring and
sandals he had set for me
then he looked inside of me and said
this is gonna hurt he placed in me a
fire with a never-ending burn
the fire would start and my heart was
spreading real fast and this fire in my
eyes and fire
in my hands when i saw next i just knew
i had to have it so i reached out and
stretched so i could grab it
i wasn't thinking about how difficult
the task could be i wasn't worried about
success or a catastrophe i wasn't even
thinking about who or what i had to be i
just
started running the baton had been
passed to me
